article.description: Hubbard leads Morgan St. past Hampton 94-92 in 2OT
article.headline: Hubbard leads Morgan St. past Hampton 94-92 in 2OT
article.linkText: Hubbard leads Morgan St. past Hampton 94-92 in 2OT
article.story: BALTIMORE -- Anthony Hubbard scored 18 points and grabbed a career-high 17 rebounds to lead Morgan State past Hampton 94-92 in double-overtime Monday night. Du'Vaughn Maxwell's offensive rebound and put-back with 7 seconds left in the second overtime pulled Hampton within 92-89. Deron Powers intentionally fouled Kyle Thomas who made 1 of 2 free throws before Brian Darden's 3-pointer cut the Pirates deficit to one, 93-92. Darden fouled Shaquille Duncan with 0.9 seconds left and he made the second of two free throw attempts. Hampton lobbed the inbounds pass near the rim and couldn't tip it in despite getting a couple sets on hands on the ball before the final buzzer. Justin Black scored 26 points, while Blake Bozeman and Donte Pretlow added 11 apiece for Morgan State (8-12, 6-2 Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference). Maxwell led Hampton (11-11, 6-3) with 25 points, 11 rebounds and five blocks. Powers added 15 and Darden 11.
